MILLS NOVELTY CO. v. INTERNATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF ICE CREAM MANUFACTURERS et al. No. 5946. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Oct. 16, 1936. Charles R. Pollard, of Washington, D. C., for appellant. Donald F. McPherson, of Chicago, 111., for appellees.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

It is ordered by the court that the motions of appellees to dismiss this appeal be, and the same are hereby, granted. Thereupon it is ordered, adjudged, and decreed that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed, with costs.
